Look what I bought yesterday.

273
00:12:59,850 --> 00:13:01,550
Your Name Means Success?

274
00:13:01,950 --> 00:13:03,800
If it's a girl, she'll be Dominika.

275
00:13:03,800 --> 00:13:04,740
And if it's a boy...

276
00:13:05,250 --> 00:13:08,880
Originally I thought Patrik, but Zbynek would be better.

277
00:13:09,150 --> 00:13:10,800
You're divorcing Zbynek, right?

278
00:13:11,350 --> 00:13:11,920
Exactly.

279
00:13:12,250 --> 00:13:13,250
It's out of spite.

280
00:13:16,130 --> 00:13:16,730
Here you go.

281
00:13:19,350 --> 00:13:20,450
Wait a moment.

282
00:13:22,250 --> 00:13:23,350
This is beer.

283
00:13:24,210 --> 00:13:24,810
Warm beer.

284
00:13:26,550 --> 00:13:27,350
Well, Bavarian.

285
00:13:28,350 --> 00:13:32,450
Simona, take this away and bring us a proper coffee.

286
00:13:34,150 --> 00:13:35,550
You people are something else.

287
00:13:38,050 --> 00:13:39,250
What's with her today?

288
00:13:42,250 --> 00:13:43,750
Don't you want to reconsider?

289
00:13:43,750 --> 00:13:44,310
No.

290
00:13:44,310 --> 00:13:49,830
Zdenicka, think about what kind of person goes to donate sperm.

291
00:13:50,250 --> 00:13:54,050
It could be some sweaty hairy primitive, for example.

292
00:13:55,050 --> 00:13:56,380
That's exactly what Zbynek told me.

293
00:13:56,380 --> 00:13:56,780
See?

294
00:13:58,390 --> 00:14:00,330
Have you teamed up with him?

295
00:14:00,450 --> 00:14:01,190
Is that what this is?

296
00:14:01,470 --> 00:14:01,510
No.

297
00:14:02,370 --> 00:14:06,870
This is exactly like that time we were deciding whether to buy a dog or a crocodile.

298
00:14:07,110 --> 00:14:09,590
I only said a poodle would fit in the car better.

299
00:14:10,050 --> 00:14:12,110
Maxime, am I your friend or Zbynek's?

300
00:14:12,530 --> 00:14:13,050
Yours.

301
00:14:13,050 --> 00:14:15,050
It doesn't look like it.

302
00:14:18,450 --> 00:14:19,530
Want milk in that?

303
00:14:23,540 --> 00:14:24,060
Fine.

304
00:14:36,080 --> 00:14:36,600
Hey.

305
00:14:36,660 --> 00:14:37,120
Hey.

306
00:14:38,190 --> 00:14:39,010
What's this?

307
00:14:40,250 --> 00:14:43,350
Ozzak disappeared for the whole day and then brought this.

308
00:14:44,150 --> 00:14:45,240
Even Vincentka, huh?

309
00:14:45,650 --> 00:14:46,150
For all of you too.

310
00:14:46,750 --> 00:14:48,080
This can't end well.

311
00:14:48,080 --> 00:14:49,040
Relax.

312
00:14:49,040 --> 00:14:50,650
How can I relax?

313
00:14:51,150 --> 00:14:57,300
Before lunch some guy in a suit showed up, said he's Pitel from the donor bank and congratulated Ozzak on his second night without drinking.

314
00:14:57,300 --> 00:14:57,820
And?

315
00:14:58,950 --> 00:15:00,250
How could he know?

316
00:15:00,950 --> 00:15:02,350
Maybe Ozzak told him.

317
00:15:03,550 --> 00:15:05,050
He read it on the internet.

318
00:15:05,550 --> 00:15:10,340
He showed me this diary where some Opossum writes about stuff happening at our house.

319
00:15:10,650 --> 00:15:12,150
That's some kind of nonsense, right?

320
00:15:12,750 --> 00:15:15,050
Everything matches perfectly.

321
00:15:15,150 --> 00:15:16,850
Just the names are different.

322
00:15:16,890 --> 00:15:17,870
Ozzak is Plzak.

323
00:15:18,660 --> 00:15:20,140
And they call me Bambelin.

324
00:15:21,450 --> 00:15:23,280
Dad, come on, are you some kind of Bambelin?

325
00:15:23,280 --> 00:15:23,640
Right?

326
00:15:24,050 --> 00:15:26,140
People are laughing at you on the internet.

327
00:15:26,550 --> 00:15:27,750
It could be someone else.

328
00:15:28,450 --> 00:15:28,950
You think?

329
00:15:30,950 --> 00:15:33,550
Uncle, should I put the rest in the fridge?

330
00:15:34,750 --> 00:15:35,850
Watch out for the fridge.

331
00:15:45,950 --> 00:15:46,750
You beast.

332
00:15:48,020 --> 00:15:49,020
Did you call Zbynek?

333
00:15:49,280 --> 00:15:53,080
Zdenicka, I... You told him to grit his teeth and get me pregnant himself.

334
00:15:54,170 --> 00:15:55,630
I'm trying to save you.

335
00:15:55,730 --> 00:15:56,370
From what?

336
00:15:56,530 --> 00:15:58,370
From your own irresponsibility.

337
00:15:58,430 --> 00:16:00,650
What's irresponsible about having a child?

338
00:16:01,010 --> 00:16:03,550
Can you imagine what it's like raising a child?

339
00:16:03,550 --> 00:16:06,010
Alone at forty, without a husband, without a gardener.

340
00:16:06,550 --> 00:16:08,230
I managed Benik, I'll manage a child.

341
00:16:08,310 --> 00:16:08,550
Sure.

342
00:16:08,950 --> 00:16:11,970
And what if Benik eats it, like that basset hound in the park?

343
00:16:12,050 --> 00:16:13,210
Benik goes to the zoo.

344
00:16:13,210 --> 00:16:14,730
And I'll turn the terrarium into a bathtub.

345
00:16:14,730 --> 00:16:17,750
Will you get rid of the child too when there are problems?

346
00:16:17,790 --> 00:16:19,290
But what problems could there be?

347
00:16:19,590 --> 00:16:21,190
I was a model child, actually.

348
00:16:21,270 --> 00:16:23,070
Maybe you, but what about the father?

349
00:16:23,070 --> 00:16:24,130
What if it takes after him?

350
00:16:24,450 --> 00:16:26,150
They said the donors are screened.

351
00:16:26,270 --> 00:16:26,670
Really?

352
00:16:28,050 --> 00:16:29,250
Take a look at this one.

353
00:16:29,550 --> 00:16:30,590
He's donating sperm too.

354
00:16:30,590 --> 00:16:31,890
He's screened too.

355
00:16:34,150 --> 00:16:34,550
See?

356
00:16:35,550 --> 00:16:36,490
They'll take anyone.

357
00:16:42,850 --> 00:16:44,750
Simona, tell my brother not to worry.

358
00:16:45,650 --> 00:16:49,050
I'll get rid of that fridge, it won't be polluting the air anymore.

359
00:16:51,150 --> 00:16:53,150
An eco-warrior who listens to opera?

360
00:16:53,850 --> 00:16:55,450
Definitely better than Zbynek.

361
00:17:09,450 --> 00:17:10,550
My God, what happened?

362
00:17:11,150 --> 00:17:12,250
He attacked the fridge.

363
00:17:13,130 --> 00:17:14,690
I told you so.

364
00:17:14,910 --> 00:17:15,650
Is he okay?

365
00:17:15,930 --> 00:17:17,530
Yeah, he just bruised his freezer compartment.

366
00:17:17,530 --> 00:17:20,290
Yeah, but I came up with a plan for Ozzak.

367
00:17:20,450 --> 00:17:23,150
I gave him a sedative, but I don't know how long it'll last.

368
00:17:23,250 --> 00:17:30,750
Hey, Dad, could you describe in detail what happened here?

369
00:17:33,050 --> 00:17:34,450
We're being bugged.

370
00:17:34,850 --> 00:17:38,050
Today I heard two girls at the bus stop talking about us.

371
00:17:38,650 --> 00:17:40,020
You're completely paranoid.

372
00:17:40,020 --> 00:17:40,520
Paranoid?

373
00:17:41,350 --> 00:17:47,370
They knew Ozzak tried Vincentka yesterday and they laughed that Bambelin is hysterical over some stupid fridge.

374
00:17:47,450 --> 00:17:48,250
Stupid!

375
00:17:48,550 --> 00:17:49,770
It cost fifteen thousand.

376
00:17:50,150 --> 00:17:54,150
So I told them that Bambelin knows what he's doing.

377
00:17:57,350 --> 00:17:58,250
Dad, calm down.

378
00:17:58,950 --> 00:18:00,480
Who would be bugging us?

379
00:18:00,750 --> 00:18:04,150
What if someone just read your little diary?

380
00:18:04,650 --> 00:18:08,050
Jesus, couldn't it be some other family where similar things happen?

381
00:18:10,480 --> 00:18:11,000
You think?

382
00:18:11,570 --> 00:18:12,270
Sure.

383
00:18:13,850 --> 00:18:17,820
You wouldn't happen to have a photo of Ozzak with the fridge, would you?

384
00:18:17,820 --> 00:18:18,920
No, why?

385
00:18:24,150 --> 00:18:27,870
Hello, I have a message for Mr. Plzak.

386
00:18:28,450 --> 00:18:29,950
You must be Bambelin, right?

387
00:18:37,150 --> 00:18:38,850
Greetings to champion Plzak.

388
00:18:39,650 --> 00:18:40,850
Hey buddy, we're all rooting for you, don't give up.

389
00:18:43,520 --> 00:18:45,620
The inmates of the addiction clinic in Bohnice.

390
00:18:46,850 --> 00:18:49,650
Wait, how did they find us?

391
00:18:49,750 --> 00:18:53,530
Well, we're not allowed to have computers, but...

392
00:18:53,530 --> 00:18:59,650
We swiped the head nurse's Nokia and got Linux running on it.

393
00:19:00,150 --> 00:19:00,550
They think they can lock us up.

394
00:19:00,550 --> 00:19:05,750
In the nuthouse, take our computers and keep us off the internet.

395
00:19:06,280 --> 00:19:06,840
Wait.

396
00:19:08,050 --> 00:19:08,950
Are you crazy?

397
00:19:10,040 --> 00:19:10,420
No.

398
00:19:10,960 --> 00:19:11,940
I'm a genius.

399
00:19:12,980 --> 00:19:13,540
Oh God.

400
00:19:14,050 --> 00:19:19,040
The alcoholics from our ward are huge fans of yours and wanted to know if you actually exist.

401
00:19:19,350 --> 00:19:23,280
So I hacked the provider and through the IP address I found out everything's being written from here.

402
00:19:23,280 --> 00:19:24,460
From this computer.

403
00:19:25,150 --> 00:19:28,550
You must be the Opossum, right?

404
00:19:30,350 --> 00:19:33,150
Iva, you're the Opossum?

405
00:19:36,430 --> 00:19:37,050
Bambelin!

406
00:19:38,480 --> 00:19:40,560
This is exactly how I imagined you.

407
00:19:40,600 --> 00:19:41,440
Completely clueless.

408
00:19:44,450 --> 00:19:47,440
You've represented us to the whole world.

409
00:19:47,440 --> 00:19:48,940
Only a few people read it.

410
00:19:49,080 --> 00:19:50,300
A few people?

411
00:19:50,850 --> 00:19:52,570
You're a total hit.

412
00:19:53,490 --> 00:19:55,550
186,522 views.

413
00:19:57,850 --> 00:20:00,630
Is everyone going to call me Bambelin now?

414
00:20:01,150 --> 00:20:02,550
Dad, don't get upset.

415
00:20:02,650 --> 00:20:03,920
Nobody will recognize you.

416
00:20:03,920 --> 00:20:06,050
What are you doing?

417
00:20:06,650 --> 00:20:09,390
I'm taking your picture with the Nokia!

418
00:20:09,390 --> 00:20:10,030
I'm a genius!

419
00:20:10,650 --> 00:20:12,250
Why are you photographing us?

420
00:20:13,610 --> 00:20:14,830
For my blog.

421
00:20:15,450 --> 00:20:16,690
Opossum and Bambelin.

422
00:20:16,810 --> 00:20:18,550
People will be clicking like crazy.

423
00:20:21,950 --> 00:20:24,850
Anyway, I've gotta run.

424
00:20:25,130 --> 00:20:26,850
You know, I don't have outing privileges today.

425
00:20:27,050 --> 00:20:28,950
The guys just threw me over the fence.

426
00:20:30,700 --> 00:20:31,940
Keep going, Opossum!

427
00:20:32,140 --> 00:20:33,380
Hang in there, Plzak!

428
00:20:33,440 --> 00:20:34,340
Don't give up, Bambelin!

429
00:20:53,240 --> 00:20:54,300
Why did you flinch?

430
00:20:55,650 --> 00:20:57,320
I wasn't expecting you here.

431
00:20:57,750 --> 00:20:58,750
Who were you expecting?

432
00:21:00,830 --> 00:21:01,390
I see.

433
00:21:03,440 --> 00:21:04,420
My little beer and...

434
00:21:04,420 --> 00:21:05,020
Don't call me that.

435
00:21:08,250 --> 00:21:09,350
Is there someone else?

436
00:21:09,350 --> 00:21:09,910
No.

437
00:21:10,750 --> 00:21:11,850
I can feel it.

438
00:21:13,150 --> 00:21:14,250
Do you have another woman?

439
00:21:14,550 --> 00:21:15,750
I don't have another woman.

440
00:21:16,250 --> 00:21:17,190
I just needed...

441
00:21:17,190 --> 00:21:17,970
What?

442
00:21:20,430 --> 00:21:20,990
A break.

443
00:21:21,610 --> 00:21:22,170
Coward!

444
00:21:22,650 --> 00:21:27,640
You can't even tell me to my face, man to man, that you've got someone else.

445
00:21:27,640 --> 00:21:28,200
I don't!

446
00:21:28,400 --> 00:21:28,640
No?

447
00:21:31,050 --> 00:21:33,050
Then what's this?

448
00:21:37,450 --> 00:21:38,050
It's so...

449
00:21:38,810 --> 00:21:39,250
humiliating.

450
00:21:40,850 --> 00:21:43,450
Everyone knew you were cheating on me and nobody told me.

451
00:21:43,700 --> 00:21:44,140
Red.

452
00:21:44,220 --> 00:21:44,860
Leave me alone!

453
00:21:47,050 --> 00:21:52,220
When you think about everything I've given you, how I kept you afloat, every time you were at rock bottom.

454
00:21:52,220 --> 00:21:53,200
And what did you give me?

455
00:21:54,160 --> 00:21:56,900
I can't stand these hysterical scenes of yours.

456
00:21:57,020 --> 00:21:58,980
Leave me alone.

457
00:21:59,200 --> 00:22:01,300
Then let me say something too, damn it.

458
00:22:01,780 --> 00:22:03,940
You think I'm doing this for fun or what?

459
00:22:04,140 --> 00:22:05,400
The doctor told me to quit you.

460
00:22:05,600 --> 00:22:07,620
And because you're listening to him, when you never listened before.

461
00:22:07,840 --> 00:22:09,080
Jesus Christ, because I have a...

462
00:22:10,670 --> 00:22:11,350
So what?

463
00:22:12,470 --> 00:22:14,030
I have a mission.

464
00:22:16,910 --> 00:22:20,890
Sure, that's you men, you start cheating and suddenly it's a mission.

465
00:22:21,030 --> 00:22:23,930
Don't take it personally, this isn't about you or me.

466
00:22:24,010 --> 00:22:25,070
It's about...

467
00:22:25,070 --> 00:22:25,910
About what?

468
00:22:28,550 --> 00:22:29,450
About metal.

469
00:22:32,050 --> 00:22:33,650
You're doing this for metal?

470
00:22:34,160 --> 00:22:34,640
Yeah.

471
00:22:36,350 --> 00:22:42,460
And what would you be willing to do for me?

472
00:22:42,460 --> 00:22:43,100
Anything.

473
00:22:44,250 --> 00:22:46,350
Like what specifically?

474
00:22:46,450 --> 00:22:47,250
Whatever.

475
00:22:47,950 --> 00:22:49,150
Would you quit drinking?

476
00:22:49,690 --> 00:22:50,170
Yeah.

477
00:22:50,750 --> 00:22:51,230
Liar.

478
00:22:51,980 --> 00:22:53,220
Want me to prove it?

479
00:22:53,540 --> 00:22:55,280
Wait, wait, what are you doing?

480
00:22:55,420 --> 00:22:57,200
No wait, for God's sake, don't do it.

481
00:22:57,280 --> 00:23:00,300
No no no, look, you're not pouring that out, you're out of your mind.

482
00:23:04,550 --> 00:23:05,950
I don't know what to do.

483
00:23:07,650 --> 00:23:10,850
Without you everything around me seems ugly.

484
00:23:11,550 --> 00:23:13,950
People are nasty and calculating beasts.

485
00:23:15,050 --> 00:23:17,950
Music screams weirdly instead of being properly loud.

486
00:23:19,350 --> 00:23:20,850
And the world is hostile.

487
00:23:21,550 --> 00:23:22,450
Complicated.

488
00:23:25,150 --> 00:23:26,450
I can't be without you either...

489
00:23:27,250 --> 00:23:28,550
I really can't.

490
00:23:31,250 --> 00:23:32,150
I won't make it.

491
00:23:35,150 --> 00:23:36,670
Honey, you'll make it.

492
00:23:36,950 --> 00:23:37,750
Honey, don't cry, don't cry.

493
00:23:38,050 --> 00:23:41,850
I can't even be without you for three days.

494
00:23:43,470 --> 00:23:44,950
Now it's only one more day.

495
00:23:45,830 --> 00:23:47,950
But it's so terribly long.

496
00:23:48,130 --> 00:23:50,130
You'll make it.

497
00:23:51,350 --> 00:23:53,060
At least then you'll look forward to seeing me.

498
00:23:53,060 --> 00:23:53,880
I already am.

499
00:23:54,650 --> 00:23:57,580
Every time I do it, I close my eyes and pretend it's you.

500
00:23:57,580 --> 00:23:58,530
Does that help?

501
00:23:59,470 --> 00:23:59,870
No.

502
00:24:01,950 --> 00:24:03,050
Remember when you...

503
00:24:03,850 --> 00:24:07,940
Once at Easter you talked me into climbing St. Vitus Cathedral and ringing the bell.

504
00:24:07,940 --> 00:24:09,660
The archbishop chased you all the way to Snely.

505
00:24:10,750 --> 00:24:11,850
He was waiting for me.

506
00:24:12,150 --> 00:24:15,750
And then we stole a tram and drove our buddies right to their buildings.

507
00:24:17,250 --> 00:24:18,950
I couldn't have done it without you.

508
00:24:19,250 --> 00:24:20,450
I couldn't have.

509
00:24:20,950 --> 00:24:25,110
But I definitely wouldn't have driven it all the way to Petrin.

510
00:24:25,110 --> 00:24:26,090
But you did.

511
00:24:28,150 --> 00:24:30,150
Because you're good.

512
00:24:31,550 --> 00:24:33,450
And you'll get through this too.

513
00:24:34,450 --> 00:24:35,150
Definitely.

514
00:24:36,750 --> 00:24:37,350
Definitely.

515
00:24:39,650 --> 00:24:40,290
Okay.

516
00:24:41,650 --> 00:24:43,740
I'll fly to you right after the doctor.

517
00:24:43,740 --> 00:24:44,760
I'll wait for you.

518
00:24:44,980 --> 00:24:45,380
Where?

519
00:24:46,650 --> 00:24:49,250
I'm hiding in the fridge under the carrots.

520
00:24:50,350 --> 00:24:51,260
That's clever.

521
00:24:51,650 --> 00:24:53,860
But it's cold and dark in here.

522
00:24:54,050 --> 00:24:55,140
The fridge is a bitch.

523
00:24:55,650 --> 00:24:56,450
Come on, I'll warm you up.

524
00:24:57,350 --> 00:24:59,750
But no drinking.

525
00:25:00,250 --> 00:25:01,150
You know me.

526
00:25:02,550 --> 00:25:03,450
As friends.

527
00:25:11,050 --> 00:25:14,550
Touch my tap and you're out of bed.

528
00:25:23,650 --> 00:25:24,150
Now you're going to go.

529
00:25:24,250 --> 00:25:27,210
And you'll write on the internet that Bambelin was right.

530
00:25:27,210 --> 00:25:27,730
You know what?

531
00:25:28,450 --> 00:25:32,650
Because Plzak really did lose it and trashed the whole apartment.

532
00:25:33,650 --> 00:25:38,550
And then Bambelin lost it and ripped the keyboard off the computer.

533
00:25:39,550 --> 00:25:43,750
It's your fault, you were encouraging him.

534
00:25:46,130 --> 00:25:49,010
And all you cared about was your clicks.

535
00:25:50,150 --> 00:25:52,410
Hello, Mr. Pacovsky, could we hide at your place?

536
00:25:52,810 --> 00:25:53,490
Why, what's happening?

537
00:25:53,690 --> 00:25:56,390
Mom closed the pub because of Mr. Ozzak and now she's home with us.

538
00:25:56,390 --> 00:25:57,130
She's taking care of us.

539
00:25:57,250 --> 00:25:58,590
She says she has to make up for what she missed.

540
00:25:58,710 --> 00:26:00,870
Yesterday we played Sorry until five in the morning.

541
00:26:00,990 --> 00:26:02,990
And since six we've been playing hide and seek.

542
00:26:04,170 --> 00:26:08,770
See what you've done?

543
00:26:10,850 --> 00:26:12,650
Hello, is Mr. Ozzak here?

544
00:26:13,350 --> 00:26:13,950
Ozzak?

545
00:26:14,450 --> 00:26:16,750
Mr. Pitel from the donor bank sent me.

546
00:26:17,490 --> 00:26:17,890
Pitel.

547
00:26:18,550 --> 00:26:19,550
The boss is waiting downstairs.

548
00:26:19,650 --> 00:26:20,050
Now?

549
00:26:20,050 --> 00:26:21,250
It's a weekday.

550
00:26:21,650 --> 00:26:24,650
It's weird, we were supposed to go to the government meeting, but he said he's coming here.

551
00:26:25,150 --> 00:26:27,950
He'd rather let the currency fall than metal.

552
00:26:28,200 --> 00:26:28,680
Metal?

553
00:26:30,880 --> 00:26:31,360
Sure.

554
00:26:31,740 --> 00:26:32,640
Can you stand up on your own?

555
00:26:33,450 --> 00:26:35,350
I'll manage, don't worry.

556
00:26:36,350 --> 00:26:37,150
And if not, the nurse will help me.

557
00:26:52,000 --> 00:26:52,480
Iva?

558
00:26:53,240 --> 00:26:53,820
What?

559
00:26:54,950 --> 00:26:56,010
Are you writing something?

560
00:26:56,010 --> 00:26:56,490
Yeah.

561
00:26:57,650 --> 00:26:58,750
You know what we agreed on?

562
00:27:00,550 --> 00:27:02,150
I'm writing a school report.

563
00:27:02,650 --> 00:27:05,350
On the loss of privacy in the digital age.

564
00:27:06,150 --> 00:27:07,150
Thank God.

565
00:27:08,750 --> 00:27:10,850
These diaries are a dangerous thing.

566
00:27:13,850 --> 00:27:17,350
Pavel Hornak once forgot his in the locker room.

567
00:27:17,650 --> 00:27:23,250
After that we all called him, well, I'll tell you when you're older.

568
00:27:31,650 --> 00:27:34,650
After those donations I was a bit weak in the knees.

569
00:27:34,750 --> 00:27:38,150
And when they figured out what was going on, they gave me an IV.

570
00:27:38,550 --> 00:27:43,050
And if you're wondering how it turned out, the doctor said he'd never seen such wild sperm in his life.

571
00:27:43,280 --> 00:27:44,640
They nearly knocked over the cup.

572
00:28:02,050 --> 00:28:03,130
You're one tough guy.

573
00:28:03,130 --> 00:28:06,030
That's what the nurse at the donations said too.

574
00:28:08,550 --> 00:28:12,450
Ten, twenty, thirty, forty, fifty.

575
00:28:12,650 --> 00:28:15,260
You saved my whole paycheck.

576
00:28:16,050 --> 00:28:17,250
Let's drink to that, shall we?
